1
00:00:00,630 --> 00:00:02,580
Instructor: Now I want to show you something

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:05,670
that is common in today's website.

3
00:00:05,670 --> 00:00:07,410
When you try to register,

4
00:00:07,410 --> 00:00:10,230
we can use another service to register,

5
00:00:10,230 --> 00:00:13,080
like Facebook, Google, LinkedIn,

6
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:16,353
and other services that enable that feature.

7
00:00:17,370 --> 00:00:22,050
Now to add that in .NET code is super, super simple.

8
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:25,950
First, we will go to facebook.developers.

9
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:30,870
I believe they have a page, developers.facebook.com.

10
00:00:30,870 --> 00:00:33,420
There, let me navigate to my apps,

11
00:00:33,420 --> 00:00:35,850
and I have few old apps here,

12
00:00:35,850 --> 00:00:38,253
but let me create a new app here.

13
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:41,730
Now here, what do we want to do?

14
00:00:41,730 --> 00:00:44,760
You might be like, let me select allow people to log in

15
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:46,620
with their Facebook account.

16
00:00:46,620 --> 00:00:48,630
But let me stop you there.

17
00:00:48,630 --> 00:00:50,850
Do not select that option.

18
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:53,370
Make sure to select other here.

19
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:56,940
And then once you select that, we have consumer,

20
00:00:56,940 --> 00:01:00,363
where we have Facebook login, let me select that.

21
00:01:01,260 --> 00:01:06,260
That is what we want, and I will give it a name of Bulky.

22
00:01:06,510 --> 00:01:08,310
Let me create that.

23
00:01:08,310 --> 00:01:10,953
I will have to enter my password.

24
00:01:12,570 --> 00:01:14,250
And great.

25
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:17,670
Right here, we want to set up the Facebook login.

26
00:01:17,670 --> 00:01:19,233
So let me select that.

27
00:01:20,130 --> 00:01:24,967
And there, we want with the www web, we need the URL.

28
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:30,980
Let me go back here, and copy the local host URL there,

29
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:35,283
paste it right here, Save and continue.

30
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:38,790
Now typically when we have to add that,

31
00:01:38,790 --> 00:01:43,230
you can see there is lots of configuration that is needed.

32
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:47,970
But thankfully, we do not have to do, because of .NET core.

33
00:01:47,970 --> 00:01:50,880
What you have to do is in Facebook login,

34
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:53,010
we will go to the Settings tab,

35
00:01:53,010 --> 00:01:54,960
and there we have to populate

36
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:57,993
this valid OAuth redirect URI.

37
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:01,680
We will paste the local host path,

38
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,960
and on top of that we will add something

39
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:07,440
called a sign in hyphen Facebook.

40
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:12,440
That is the default valid OAuth redirect URI for Facebook.

41
00:02:13,380 --> 00:02:14,610
Now when you publish,

42
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:17,310
you will have to give more access here,

43
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:19,953
but for testing, this is all okay.

44
00:02:20,995 --> 00:02:24,180
With that configured, let me save the changes here.

45
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:26,340
And then we will go to Settings.

46
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:28,203
We have the basic settings.

47
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,870
Now similar to Stripe,

48
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:35,640
we have an app ID and app secret for Facebook.

49
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:39,630
We will have to configure that in our application.

50
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:43,230
Now, previously in the old days of .NET core,

51
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:45,480
Facebook, Google, and all of them

52
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:48,510
were included in the .NET package,

53
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:50,640
but now they have separated that.

54
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:52,380
So on the web project,

55
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:56,250
we will select Manage NuGet Packages.

56
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,040
Let me close everything else here.

57
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:01,260
And the package that we want to search for

58
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:06,260
is microsoft.aspnet.core.authentication.facebook.

59
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:12,390
Perfect, we have that package here.

60
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:16,173
Let me include the pre-release, and install that.

61
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,770
Great, that package is installed.

62
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:25,980
Let me see what I have in the Updates tab here.

63
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:27,390
That's okay.

64
00:03:27,390 --> 00:03:29,040
Let me close that.

65
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:29,873
And with that,

66
00:03:29,873 --> 00:03:33,423
we have added the support for Facebook authentication.

67
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,060
Now, last thing that we have to do

68
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:39,090
is add and configure that in our project.

69
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:42,960
And what is the file that we will use for configuration?

70
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:46,383
If you said Program.cs, you are correct.

71
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:48,570
On builder here,

72
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:53,280
we will say builder.Services.Add Authentication.

73
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:57,030
And we want to add the Facebook authentication,

74
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:58,620
because of the package,

75
00:03:58,620 --> 00:04:00,930
now we have this option here,

76
00:04:00,930 --> 00:04:03,663
and there we have to configure a few option.

77
00:04:04,830 --> 00:04:06,633
First one is option.AppId,

78
00:04:08,257 --> 00:04:10,860
and that we will provide from the portal.

79
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:14,040
On top of that, we also have the AppSecret,

80
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:17,313
that also we will have to fetch from the portal.

81
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:21,600
So, let me switch back to the portal.

82
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,460
Copy the app ID.

83
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:25,830
Paste it right here.

84
00:04:25,830 --> 00:04:30,830
And I will copy the AppSecret, paste that right here.

85
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:33,480
With that three lines of code,

86
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,460
let me run the application

87
00:04:35,460 --> 00:04:38,073
and see if something is different now.

88
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:43,560
And to your surprise, if you go to register this time,

89
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,963
you will see a button for Facebook.

90
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:49,910
Now if you click on the button here...

91
00:04:50,850 --> 00:04:53,820
Perfect, you can see Bulky is requesting access

92
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:57,690
to name, profile picture, and email address.

93
00:04:57,690 --> 00:05:01,050
Now if I select Continue as Bhrugen here,

94
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:04,290
it will redirect and take me back to the website

95
00:05:04,290 --> 00:05:07,380
based on the redirect URI that we gave.

96
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:08,670
And perfect.

97
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:11,310
It says you've been successfully authenticated

98
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,600
with Facebook.

99
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:17,460
Please enter an email address and click the Register button.

100
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:21,510
Now do not press the register button right here.

101
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:25,323
Because if we open this URL in the other window.

102
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:30,210
Right here, you will notice on the register page

103
00:05:30,210 --> 00:05:32,970
we are asking for many more fields.

104
00:05:32,970 --> 00:05:36,780
But on this page, it only has the email.

105
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:39,210
So we have to modify this page

106
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:42,450
to handle the other fields as well.

107
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:46,080
Only after that, hit the Register button.

108
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:50,490
So we have to go to identity, account, external login,

109
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:53,313
and let me do that in the next video.

